his other than sorry the whole event occured.<br><br>Riders has a really lax recruiting policy right now which is how members who don't follow and abide by the laws of the guild get into the mix.  Most of out members in the 35 to 40 range have been brought up in our younger guild Riders Chosen.<br><br>RC was formed ad a pre-screening method to recruit lower levels and bring them up into Riders.  The problem is that RotA and RC do not have a good communication with each other right now and we graduate members as soon as they hit 35 and don't find out if they really fit into RotA.  I think this is where Laaw came from.  <br><br>I guess this post overall is a message to both you and myself about RotA and to give us all a wake up call.<br><br>Thanks for your time<br><br>Danxor Danger<br>Officer of RotA<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ubinoche.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Binoche</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://home.earthlink.net/~medicnman71/_uimages/healer.jpg BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>w4nn4b3!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/29/01 5:18:38 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~medicnman71/_uimages/BinRuby2.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sorry for slow response</span><hr size=1> I dont fault the RoA for not checking their boards, running a guild is very tough indeed. I also have grouped with many honorable RoA's. This is the main reason I didnt name RoA in this thread. I appreciate your time in looking at this matter, as all our time in EQ is precious. <br><br>Once again, thank you for your attention and response.<br><br>Binoche <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uiwonders.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IWonders</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b!</span><br> <font color=#000033>(1/29/01 5:22:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Laaw -  Iskar monk, ninja looter</span><hr size=1> Sigh!  I also hate putting someone on the Shit List, and have debated doing so for the last few days.<br><br>I was in Unrest with a Shaman pulling from the second floor (Hand and Magus) when I 'heard' the shout from Laaw needing help in the barroom (I was the warrior you saw helping him).  A little bit later he came out to where we were asking for help with a spawn, saying it would be good loot and experience.  Now, if he would have said he needed to kill it for a monk quest or something of that nature, I would have helped him right away.  As it was, the shaman and I were already grouped and had our little niche on the playing field <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and quite happy with it.  But, he kept asking for our help until I finally said yes and in we went.<br><br>It went downhill from there.... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    We met on the second floor and he asked if someone had a GLS and to give it to him, wtf?!?  If he knew he needed a GLS, why didn't he bring one with him?  He never explained why he needed it, just that he did.  In my stupidity, I gave him one of mine to get the ball rolling.  Now he never said the stone would be 'lost' triggering the spawn (Abomination) although I suspected it would, but it would have been nice to have been told.  Let me say this; the GLS or it's cost really mean nothing to me, if it is needed for a group activity, I would gladly give it up.  BUT I would have liked to know why!!<br><br>After he triggered the Abomination, he started running around the house and grounds 